Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Most amazing meal and service. Have been looking forward to eating here and it didn't disappoint.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Great food. Excellent service

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Never disappoints!   Food and service were excellent.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: One of the best meals we’ve had! The service was outstanding. We wanted to catch a glimpse of the Neowise comet and when we told the hostess, she wrote us a list of viewing spots in the area to try. Amazing food and drinks, amazing people.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Simply put, Al Tavalo is our favorite place to eat. Wonderful service, great waiters and servers, ambiance and food that are second to none.  We eat there at least once a month.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: A s always, A Wonderful Anniversary Dinner!!!!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Best restaurant in CT by far. Such a special place.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Wonderful, as always. Such a treat. Though we were closer to the road because they have added outdoor seating, it was such a wonderful meal.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Excellent, as always! I’d love to see bigger olives in the martinis, with a blue cheese stuffed option :). Servers are impeccably trained, and were amazing.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: Unforgettable! Everything was splendid. We can’t wait for our next chance to return.

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: The best food in the Litchfield Hills -- as good as the best restaurants in NYC and other large/gourmet cities. The staff is friendly and accommodating. A little pricey, but the experience is worth every penny. Keep up the excellent work!

Name: Arethusa al Tavolo
Comments: We had an amazing experience . Service was perfect. Food exquisite We made another reservation to come back in a few weeks. Very impressed all around

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Doing a great job with outdoor dining -  but why on earth are servers in long sleeves plus ties and managers wearing jackets??  Get these folks some short sleeve shirts!!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: I do not normally leave reviews but I was disappointed overall in the experience. While our server was great, both in my party had to send back the steaks because they were overcooked-all gray color in a Med Rare steak. As we finished the recooked meal, it appeared we were being rushed and ultimately while trying to order another round of drinks were told by a nervous waiter that we had to leave because of the time limit on the table. Mind you it was 9 and they closed at 10 (no one really seen waiting) and we were still drinking and contemplating dessert, and again, had earlier had to wait 20+ minutes for new steaks and sides. The waiter again apologized but said it was a management rule and claimed they were booked later as he presented us with our check. Nothing removed for the food issue and a check of $450 to which we noted once more would be more and were dumbfounded that a restaurant would not continue to serve two people spending this amount, to which he nodded and appeared embarrassed. I know this is the era of COVID where we are told we should just be thankful for the restaurant to be open but this was not a positive experience, especially for the price.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Simply amazing

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Loved this restaurant.  Shocked that I was able to find something so amazing without anyone recommending it.  I took a chance on Open Table and the hit was a great one.Chef is from Sicily.  Restaurant located in a former home in Venice, and is absolutely charming. The wait staff and all were very attentive and the food could not have been more delicious.  Not inexpensive, but worth every dollar.  Delish!  I will go back again and again.Oh, and they had the social distancing down pat, having put up trellises in a variety of places with ivy and flowers on them.  Really charming place.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Authentic Italian food. Best pasta in town. Great outdoor seatimg. Fabulous wine selection!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Everything was delicious!

Name: Bones
Comments: Great way to celebrate our anniversary! Food was delicious and service was GREAT!

Name: Bones
Comments: All around excellent experience. Went for my wife’s birthday! We loved it. Will be back.

Name: Bones
Comments: This is our second trip to Bone’s since reopening and the waiters, servers, concierge are all wearing masks and socially distancing tables with an empty adjacent to you.   Always outstanding and the team is impeccable!

Name: Bones
Comments: Bones is one of my favorite restaurants in Atlanta, especially for an awesome steak. My most recent visit I was not impressed at all with my Filet as it was too bland. My partner LOVED the porterhouse as it had a lot of flavor. The lobster tails were good. Dessert always amazing. It just didn't blow me away the last visit. I'll definitely go back just disappointed with the last visit.

Name: Bones
Comments: Great to back there and take a friend from out of town that had never been🥋

Name: Bones
Comments: The service was wonderful. Our waiter was friendly and attentive. I had the lobster, macaroni and cheese, and greens. It was divine. Margaritas were on point too.

Name: Bones
Comments: The service was impeccable. All of our steaks were cooked to perfection. The sides were delicious and well portioned. Fantastic experience all the way around.

Name: Bones
Comments: Phenomenal food and personalized service, as always! We were celebrating my husband’s 50th birthday and they had a private room set up for our group. The table was decorated with confetti and the menus were personalized with his name! Very special! We enjoyed our evening very much! Because of Covid, the restaurant was skipping every other table and all staff were wearing tight fitting masks. I didn’t see a single employee remove their mask even once, or pull it below their nose. At all! Felt very safe.

Name: Bones
Comments: Perfect as always

Name: Bones
Comments: Food was great, I did feel rushed though. Appreciate the complimentary champagne and dessert but would have rather looked at the menu and chose my own dessert. Would have appreciated an after dinner drink too but felt rushed to get out

Name: Bones
Comments: Great food, great service, fantastic wine list and great environment.

Name: Bones
Comments: Bones is the best! Everything is perfect from start to finish.

Name: Bones
Comments: A great place to go for a special dinner!  The steaks were cooked perfectly, and the sides were delicious!  We recommend the Bones salad, lobster bisque soup, hash browns (they were very unique), mushrooms (great compliment to the steaks), and grilled asparagus.

Name: Bones
Comments: It was my first time. It was a business dinner. I will return.

Name: Bones
Comments: Perfect steakhouse experience, nothing is better than Bones - food, service, and the ambiance!  There are lots of upscale steak places in Atlanta but Bones is the best.

Name: Bones
Comments: It was one of the best dining experiences ever! Service, food, atmosphere...Foie gras app out of this world, rib eye so tender, truffle mash potato delicious...service attentive...wine list great! Dessert was great, idk how we still had room for it!

Name: Buccan
Comments: Silver Weddings

Name: Buccan
Comments: Buccan never disappoints.  Great Food.  Great Service.  Great Environment.  Call for a reservation though.  It's hard to get in if you're not proactive.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Delicious options on a intriguing menu. Excellent staff, and overall a wonderful experience. It is quite loud, which makes it a challenge to hear the server and the company I was with.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Amazing!!!

Name: Buccan
Comments: From beginning to end an absolutely stellar experience.

Name: Buccan
Comments: Good foodReally GoodFood

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: One of the top restaurants in Scottsdale! Itâ€™s a must go!

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: Very romantic atmosphere. Service was awesome. The best food we have ever had so delicious every course. The waiter was so informed on food and wine. It was our wedding anniversary and we loved out experience.

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: Great food but better service! one of the best dining experiences in Phoenix

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: This was my first time and won't be my last!! We had looked to come here before and why we did not I am not sure. Our server Kyle was wonderful and very knowledgeable. We enjoyed every aspect of the meal the course selections were beautiful the presentation and flavors exceeded. I can't wait to bring my husband back.

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: This place is definitely a photo shoot spot if you're looking for a romantic, warm and cozy place to start an unforgettable night date. The service was impeccable started with the wine pairing from the extensive list.  It's a 4-course dinner menu with least two options per course, but you can get Ã  la carte if you sit at the bar. For pricing, everything is determined by the fourth course of your choosing. I chose the "Dijon Brushed New Zealand Lamb Rack" which was $120. While my mother (whom I brought for long-overdue Mother's Day dinner) ordered the "Niman Ranch USDA Prime Ribeye" which was $135. The other three courses are included in that price. We also ordered the add-on "Hudson Valley Foie Gras" which was out of this world--my mom loved it so much that she wouldn't save any for me. Dessert is extra, ours were $12 each. The dessert menu includes not only cakes but sorbets, dessert cocktails, coffee, grappa, digestifs, cordials, dessert wine and more.

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: Great food, great staff and the ambience was fantastic. Highly recommend.

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: Excellent as always!!  The entire staff was exceptional!  Food was superb...we keep coming back because Monarch truly is the best in Phoenix!

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: Amazing food - best service!

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: Fabulous food, service and atmosphere.  Thank you to John and Juan and everyone at Cafe Monarch.  We will be back.

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: Cafe Monarch is always an amazing experience and tonight did NOT disappoint!

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: The entire staff was outstanding. The restaurant exudes total style and class. The food far exceeded my high expectations and the Chilean Sea Bass was the best piece of fish I have ever eaten.

Name: Café Monarch
Comments: Beautiful and delicious restaurant.  The service was first rate and the cuisine was of the highest caliber.  Our bill was approximately $200 a person with tip.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: It certainly lives up to its reputation! The food was of the highest quality we have found in Kansas City, among the top-tier restaurants. Service was top-notch and everything was better than we expected. We will definitely be back.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Wonderful as usual

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: This is a lovely place. The food was great and the ambience was relaxing. They fully decorated the empty tables with little vignettes. It was a nice touch.

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Café Provence sets the standard of excellence in KC region. The food, flavors, presentation, creativity, and attentive staff are always wonderful.. C’est magnifique!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: Amazing food, service!  I want to come all the time!

Name: Cafe Provence
Comments: First time we tried Cafe Provence and it was very good.  Highly recommend.  We really enjoyed it and will definitely be back.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Patio dining at Chez Billy Sud is the way to go during the pandemic. Gracious and attentive service and delicious, well-prepared food make Chez Billy Sud a welcome oasis.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: It was terribly hot on the patio, but that could not be helped. Our waitresswas really wonderful and I know it was really HOT for her, because she neverstopped working! The food was excellent. Happy to have you all opened again.I will be back...but after the sun goes down! Thanks!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: We had been trying to eat at Chez Billy Sud’s for the past 2 years, but for different reason or another we hadn’t been.  Well, we finally made it on Friday!  All the expectations were reached!  Food, ambiance and service were great!  Call out to our waiter!!!Even Mother Nature with  a little bit of a breeze on an 80+ degree evening.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Great. The service was the best.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Had a great time dining outside here.  Great location!

Name: Coppa
Comments: Good experience

Name: Coppa
Comments: We ate here during Covid and had an awesome experience celebrating my wife's birthday. Outdoor seating was quite nice, albeit we sat on the Shawmut St side, so not as private (we felt stared at by cars stopping on the stop sign).Food was fantastic as usual. I just wish they had more options for wine by the glass.Regardless of where you go during COVID, go with patience and an open mind. Everyone is trying their best. With that, you will have an awesome experience and not get bothered by the little things (which I won't note here for this same specific reason).There were no COVID related hygiene issues as all customer facing staff had masks and gloves on. Also very strict rules around using the bathroom. Be ready to put on gloves and wait.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Loved being about to 'dine out' again at Coppa. It's one of my favorite restaurants and didn't disappoint! This was my first experience eating outside and the whole Coppa team managed it beautifully.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Food was delicious.  Serving sizes were perfect: left totally satiated without feeling overly full. Staff was very polite. Only negative was that our waitress kind of ignored us after our initial order, e.g. didn't refill our water; had to flag her down to get another drink. We would have loved one final drink, but she just dropped off the check and left us to be. Slightly expensive - for pasta - but that's expected. Overall a nice Sat night, al fresco dining experience.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Perfect spot on a hot summer day in the South End.  The Frose was perfection!

Name: Coppa
Comments: Great food. Great service. Great job with improv setup outdoors.

Name: Coppa
Comments: Great food as always.  Outside dining area top notch

Name: Coppa
Comments: Great food, perfect atmosphere, attentive and knowledgeable staff

Name: Coppa
Comments: Service and food are incredible - love this restaurant!

Name: Coppa
Comments: First restaurant meal in 4 months. Outside tables well-spaced. Very professionally and safely run. Excellent food and polite service, as always. Monday meatball sub is outstanding.

Name: Daniel
Comments: This was our second visit to Restaurant Daniel in 2 years. The food was still "ok" there was nothing amazing that blew me away like other Michelin restaurants we've been to. There is no taste to the meats except for the sauces which they are doused in. The staff was good.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Eating outside at Daniel was a unique experience. But it was a pleasant one. People worked hard to make it as restaurant-like as possible, and, frankly, being deprived of a decent restaurant experience for so many months, it was wonderful. Go enjoy!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Excellent job on outdoor dining during the age of Rona.  Very thankful to have FWD here in Manhattan Beach providing excellent raw seafood, and innovative seafood dishes!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Great ambience. & food for a social distance dinner!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: We were a party of 3 celebrating on of our birthdays. The staff was wonderful, taking every precaution during this pandemic. Our waitress never re-touched anything that was opened, there was a separate bus staff. The food was amazing. We had oysters, grilled octopus, the Halibut ceviche and all split the lobster roll. All so good. The staff even brought out a complimentary dessert-Key Lime Pie that was equally amazing. Thanks FWD for a wonderful evening!!!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: 30th birthday! FWD always does a great job with each aspect of our experience. The food, the presentation, the feels, the drinks, service and recommendations. 5* all the way.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Love love love this place. The food is delicious and the service is wonderful.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Great atmosphere on the new patio. Food is definitely over priced  but the quality is good and it’s great to support our local businesses.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Always excellent.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Love the outdoor dining. The food was phenomenal as always.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Fresh seafood, amazing cocktails and key lime pie to die for - what else could you want?!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: I took my son for a special dinner to celebrate and we had a spectacular time. Our reservation was for 645pm and when we checked in with the hostess she let us know that our table would be ready soon but that they were waiting for the prior reservations to clear out. After waiting about 15 minutes the hostess brought over  a delicious Peruvian scallops appetizer as a treat for us having to wait for our table to be available. We felt this was a very nice touch and the kick off to a fantastic evening filled with scrumptious food and great service. Due to the Covid all of the seating was outside now which was actually amazingly comfortable especially when it cooled off a little in the evening and the heater lamps were brought out. We felt the service and the food were fantastic and we will definitely be back soon.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Love this restaurant but they are struggling with service and wait time right now. I understand that times are tough at the moment but we were seated almost an hour after our reservation time and our food took FOREVER to come out. Our server was not very attentive either. I guess I’ll have to wait until things are back to normal before I dine here again.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Vacation with sister

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Wonderful dining experience! Our server, Michelle V was phenomenal and the food was delicious and imaginative. Kudos to the chef for the outstanding Peruvian scallops! The oysters were fresh and flavorful. Hubby had the soft shell crab, son had the lobster roll and I had the fried oyster roll and crab chowder. It had lots of clams in it, still in the shell!! The key lime pie was just the right tartness and ended our meal perfectly. Our first time here and will definitely return soon.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Need a boost to your mood?  FWD!  Late lunch on the new patio was fabulous!!  Breezes, sunshine, and amazing food.  Had BOTH specials!!  Santa Barbara Prawns and Grilled Hamachi Collar.  I ate like a cat, they were so good!  Virtual hugs to Rachel, Sal, and Chef Alice.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: My favorite restaurant in Manhattan Beach is now even better with amazing outside seating!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: The Lobster Roll is AWESOME. Oysters are very fresh. Great outdoor dinning experience.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: It's a great fine dining experience as you'd expect; good food, good wine, attentive service. However, our server's mask kept sliding down below his nose when he was talking to us or bringing food over, so we were really on edge the whole time about sanitary concerns.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Great outdoor dining experience.  Superior service and food.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Great job of creating an outdoor dining space in the parking lot. Nice ambiance. I had the Caesar salad which was very over dressed - a big surprise. Also had the salmon. The waiter didn’t ask me how I wanted it prepared and it was overdone to my taste. Overall the food was a disappointment.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Excellent set up for COVID outdoor dining. Food was very good, but not as outstanding as the price tag suggests. Steak was sold strongly to us but was underwhelming. The carpaccio was the best!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Excellent!

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Once again a great dinner on the patio.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Superb in every way. Great menu options. Lovely setting. Peaceful. Outstanding service.  We are foodies and would recommend to the same.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: Best food and best service, EVER! No more need be said.

Name: Geronimo
Comments: what a wonderful evening!  We sat outdoors (per the gov) on the portal.  It was lovely.  Began with wonderful drinks.  Moved on to appetizers, entree, etc.  The food was delicious, service attentive but not hovering.  Valet was personable and so helpful.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: We came to celebrate a birthday and had a fabulous experience. The ambiance and service are great, and the food will not disappoint! Highly recommend!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Every morsel put in front of me exploded with flavor and mind blowing deliciousness. I highly recommend the sautÃ©ed green beans and pork shank.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Amazing food and service. This was a birthday dinner for my wife and they made it amazing.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Great food and place!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: It was below average. Theyâ€™re not adapting to covid and dining restrictions well. Their seating capacity is pretty weather related, so adjust accordingly. Weâ€™re all adults, we understand the current pandemic, if you donâ€™t have the seating available call an hour or two before and cancel the reservation. Donâ€™t act like the guest has a problem when they arrive to the restaurant.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: I loved that the seating was spaced out, before I always felt like I was sitting on top of the table next to me. Having one more room between tables made the experience even more enjoyable!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Delicious as always!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Good food ! But due to covid AC was off so it was hot inside. Great service overall

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Everything at Girl and Goat was phenomenal! The food was gorgeous and delicious!! And the front of house staff was so gracious and hospitable. One of our favorite places in the city!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Fantastic!! As usual. Delicious, friendly. Our favorite restaurant

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Has to be in the top 10 disappointments I have ever had at a restaurant.  The food was mediocre.  The service was pretentious.  We could not have been more unhappy with what was supposed to be a great restaurant.  There are certainly challenges in todayâ€™s world and restaurants are especially impacted.  But even if the food was a disappointment there is no excuse for the service, both at the front door and server.   I hate it when people act like they are doing you a favor by taking care of you and doing their job.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: It was 92 degrees outside and incredibly humid, we had reservations and sat indoors and the ac was not running, we were sweating through our clothes and extremely uncomfortable the entire time, almost ruining the experience. Food was wonderful, but nobody from the restaraunt acknowledged the intense heat and humidity that the wait staff and clientele had to suffer through. All windows were shut and it was extremely uncomfortable for women and men, no circulation. Food was amazing though, itâ€™s too bad.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: There is no wow factor. Food is very good but not great.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Great Job Girl & the Goat! This was one of my first times dining out since COVID and it was a wonderful experience. Everyone wore masks, gloves, and kept their distance. The food was great and loved the add ins of local in-season ingredients! Thanks for making us feel safe.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Me & the lady went out for a nice little date night. Everything went smooth from start to finish with our reservation. They even bring your food out to you from lightest to heaviest which I liked. We got the shrimp & gotham greens salad... FIRE! We got the goat empanadas... AMAZING!!! & we also got the Kalbi style short ribs... ON POINT!! For dessert we got the caramel corn & malt balls & the Berries & creme which were both equally SUPERB! It was also very comforting that all the employees were wearing masks & everyone was spread apart. Iâ€™m definitely going back without hesitation

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Good food. Great service but SO HOT INSIDE it made it difficult to enjoy our food.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Too hot inside restaurant- no air

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Girl and the Goat is a spectacular restaurant and like all restaurants in the city, they are having to make changes that effects the experience. They deserve our support. They are doing a good job in difficult times and when we go back to normal they will be flawless again, no doubt!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Outstanding, amazing, one of a kind. Definitely worth it for a date night or special occasion with unique food and ambiance. 10/10

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Food was great - ordered the crab rangoon, halibut and branzino.  Everything tasted great - one minor issue was that the skin on branzino fish was overcharred. We were celebrating a birthday and got dessert on the house as a special treat.  We expected to be seated outside but got only inside seating.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Mis handling of a reservation and being verbally attacked by a random waiter ruined the evening. Unprofessional and indifferent interaction.Dismissive managers of the situation and careless handling of customers makes it difficult to support this local restaurant. Specially when there are many more that need support.A $250+ dinner for two people was ruined by lack of respect and care.The food was really good!But due to the poor customer service will not be returning.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Everything absolutely a mouth watering delight!Loved the mixture of flavors and variety of choices.  It was absolutley delicious!

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Went here for husbandâ€™s birthday dinner. Glad they were open during this pandemic! I liked the safety measures they took to make sure everyone was alright.

Name: Girl & the Goat
Comments: Great! Very chill and felt clean and safe!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: As always, excellent refined food with a comfortable neighborhood feel. We love this place. They did an excellent job with safety and health measures. So glad this was our first indoor dining experience in 5 months.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Love this place! They did a great job at making us feel like we were not taking a risk i dining out!

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Food was delicious except the bucatini was a little overdone. The sauce was very good and you can tell it was made in-house. Drinks were well-made. Service was great and everyone was very nice.

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Probably the best dinner we’ve had in Cambridge since Covid hit Michael the chef and Trevor the host do an amazing jobDon and Diana

Name: Giulia Restaurant
Comments: Normally not so quiet but we enjoyed it. Food as always is terrific but due to fewer patrons we enjoyed a relaxing dinner with great food and service.

Name: Hersh's
Comments: Excellent pizza and dessert. Would recommend to everyone!

Name: Seafood
Comments: NYC price for Chicago location. You got what you pay for. There’s something for everyone. I was with my mom and my sister, got a last minute reservation here. Food is top notch. Well done fillet mignon that is really soft and easy to cut with a knife. Usually I get a dry or rubbery steak for a well done, but their steak takes the top spot. Crab cakes and chicken were also outstanding as well. It is well worth the splurge if you’re feeling fancy or need to celebrate a special occasion.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Everyone’s food was absolutely wonderful. I can’t wait to go back!

Name: Seafood
Comments: As always stwlkar food, stellar service.  It was sad seeing a once vibrant place so empty due to covid, but its a legend for a reason

Name: Seafood
Comments: I had called ahead of time and asked about social distancing and wearing masks.  I was more than amazed to hear what they were doing for customers and for their staff safetyWe ate there and never felt unsafe or anxious during our meal.  Would recommend it to anyone and I have .

Name: Seafood
Comments: High quality stone crabs and steaks. Awesome service!

Name: Seafood
Comments: Love everything about joes From the service to the food it it all top notchOne of my family’s favorite restaurantsWould highly recommend

Name: Seafood
Comments: Excellent food and service!  The ambience was excellent.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Our family has been going to Joe's for many years & the service and food  always good.  Joe's always seems to make our visit feel as something special from entry to the restaurant thru dinner and always a thank you for visiting their restaurant

Name: Seafood
Comments: Good food. Really good food. The service was great my first time and spotty this time.

Name: Seafood
Comments: I cannot say enough about Joe's.  Even after recovering from the shutdowns related to COVID, they came back better!  Service was amazing, the GM Paul Ritchie went out of his way to make our experience phenomenal and they added several new restaurant items.  They are very successful and people will come, yet Joe's goes out of its way to thank you as the customer for coming!

Name: Seafood
Comments: Every thing was amazing food,the customer service just everything

Name: Seafood
Comments: No outside dining but they massively social distanced the tables. It feel odd and sort of depressing but we salute the effort. The food was fabulous as always and our server Denise was perfect.

Name: Seafood
Comments: This place is excellent in terms of taste and service. The only place in Chicago so far where we felt comfortable dining in. tables set far enough apart (like about 20 feet rather than just the 6 foot minimum). Servers were on things immediately. From filling water glasses (without making any contact with anything), filling wine and always setting the bottle down carefully and label towards us. checked back when needed but not so often it was irksome. Really knew when to be there and when not too.The collection of seafood is fresh and outstanding. We sampled Shrimp, Lobster, Crab, & Scallops and everything was good. Wine list is extensive and had unique choices for pretty fair pricing. Know up front that you will probably spend a couple hundred for a good meal here, but it WILL be good and you WILL feel treated special and safe from start to finish. There's a lot of classy seafood places in River North, but this one scored all the way through for us.

Name: Seafood
Comments: My ahi tuna was over cooked and bland.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Annual birthday dinner for my daughter and her boyfriend.  This has been our tradition for the past 3 years, and it's their favorite place to come and celebrate.  We came during Covid and they took all the necessary safety precautions which included masks, gloves, social distancing, 25% occupancy, etc.  Was a little strange, as we are used to seeing it very busy and having tables crammed together, but the service and food were as outstanding as always.

Name: Seafood
Comments: We have been Joes diners for years. This meal was best ever. Steak, sides and crab legs perfect. Service was terrific.

Name: Seafood
Comments: Everything was cooked perfectly and explained very well to help with my perfect Halibut selection.

Name: Seafood
Comments: We felt very welcome and safe while dining at Joe's, with the COVID-19 requirements. As always the food and service were outstanding. Looking forward to our next visit.

Name: Seafood
Comments: I can't say enough about Jennifer at Joe's.  She was a knowledgeable, pleasant,  and has awesome customer service.   I am so pleased about my experience. This was my first time there and I will be going again.  Awesome experience

Name: Seafood
Comments: We are Lettuce Entertain You regulars, and Joe's is one of our favorite places.  We are always extremely satisfied with their excellence!

Name: Koi
Comments: What a great place! Ambiance, service, food - everything was top notch!

Name: Koi
Comments: Enjoyed the patio COVID safe experience. Same great service and food.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: The restaurant did a great job in the lockdown by setting up tables on the tented side patio.  Even with a limited menu and wine list we had a great meal with great service.  Will be back again soon

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Kudos to the restaurant and staff. In this era of COVID they know how to serve and make one comfortable.  I would go back again without hesitation.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Love L’Auberge - highly recommended for a fantastic meal and service.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: They did a very nice job of dining outside under a tent at 90degree heat

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: we have dined at L'Auberge Chez Francois many times before. This was our first restaurant dinner since we began to stay home under the Covid pandemic. The restaurant took all necessary precautions to protect staff and diners.As always the service and the ambience were excellent. The only disappointment was the heirloom tomato salad which Was drowning in dressing and the tomatoes were less than satisfactory.Otherwise the four of us were very happy with our dinners and of course we will go back.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Had a wonderful lunch for our first time visit. We can't wait to go back again, (when its not so hot outside),  to sit in their beautiful outside seating.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Amazing setting - wonderful ambience and service. And of course the food is top notch. Feels like being back in France!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Excellent. We will  be back. Very happy to see the whole staff being very careful with masks and gloves.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Wonderful but not what it’s always been the 36 years I’ve been going. I’m sure the impact of Covid is a key factor, from reduced menu offerings to too spaced apart table arrangements and very good but not exquisite fare. I know Jacque is working harder than ever to preserve the family legacy and I greatly appreciate him. I’ll keep coming back for certain.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Food is still excellent, but the general well cared for , extras, we've grow to expect were lacking.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Four of us ladies thoroughly enjoyed the afternoon in the garden under a canopy. It was a warm afternoon, yet we remained quite comfortable. It was an outstanding luncheon for a special occasion.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Always a lovely meal and the patio this evening was a joy

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: A wonderful lunch on the tented patio!  Multiple fans cooled us off a a day with the heat index nearing 100.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Another wonderful lunch with family for memories

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Superb meal. Lunch in the beautiful outdoor garden. Wells paced tables under a large tent provides shade and rain protection. Excellent service as always!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: This is one our favorite restaurants in the area. The food, service, and ambience will never disappoint.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: This is our first return visit since the start of the pandemic and it was better than ever!   The restaurant has installed a large canvas pavilion over the outdoor dining area,  Tables are at least 8 feet apart and servers wear masks and gloves.  Menus are only used once and then recycled or destroyed.  We felt safe and relaxed the entire time.The food was outstanding.  Try the duxelles crepe appetizer and the heirloom tomato salad.  The beef Bourguignon and the Halibut with buerre blanc were both perfect.  We are so glad you are back.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Chez Francois is simply the best.  The restaurant has taken precautions to make dining safe and enjoyable. The patio dining was perfect!  Our favorite!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Always a treat to come here & I always order the chateaubriand!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: It was a birthday celebration

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: The service was great, many accommodations in place to meet social distancing requirements which made us feel comfortable being there in this crazy time.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Superb service as always and the food was great as well.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: My wife and I had a very pleasant dining experience for our anniversary.  The food was superb and the service as usual was great.  Highly recommend this restaurant - especially for a 'special' meal.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: La Grotta is an outstanding Italian restaurant with a beautiful outside patio and with delicious entree choices.  My wife and I have been regular customers for over 30 years and have never had a bad experience.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Excellent place! Went there for my wifeâ€™s birthday!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: It was a special occasion indeed and LaGrotta made it so! Dining in the elegant dining room with such attentive service and delicious food is always a pleasure!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Came here with my wife for our anniversary, and everything was perfect. The food was very delicious and very affordable.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: 5 star experience and great value for the food and atmosphere. A classic Atlanta restaurant that we love to visit!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Incredible restaurant!!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: My wife and I have been going to La Grotta for special occasions since the 1980's when we were in high school and college.  I don't believe we have ever had a bad meal!  The decor is old school and most people dress up.  Our appetizers and entrees were very good.  We are planning to go back in a few weekends for my mother in law's 80th.  Can't wait!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Our waiter just wasnâ€™t that good.  But he thought he was.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Best service of any restaurant. Food was tremendous.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: We had another fabulous meal last night at Le Bilboquet. Thank you as always - great food, great service, just one of the best dining experiences in Dallas.  Wonderful menu. We enjoy sitting outside on the patio. Service was wonderful, yet quiet and respectful. Cajun Chicken still one of the favorites in our family. Worth the trip. You will not be disappointed.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: It’s one of my top three restaurants in town! Never disappoints.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Le Bib is one of our favorite restaurants.  Edward and Stephan deliver a top notch dining experience every time.  Highly recommend!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: 50th Wedding Anniversary celebration! Excellent everything!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: The food was okay, not worth the price. Service was very slow and not very attentive. We eat out at least 7 times a month all around the metroplex. We probably won’t be back.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Very fine dining experience.  In fact, the best in Dallas.  Professionalism at its finest!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: We have eaten in restaurants 2 times in the last few months and we have chosen Bilboquet both times. We felt very comfortable with the set up and service. The food was delicious as always. A real treat to be out.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Great as always!  A neighborhood gem!

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: One of my favorites! Wonderful place to dine, food is great, friendly service and beautiful atmosphere.

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Dallas institution

Name: Le Bilboquet - Dallas
Comments: Le Bilboquet is wonderful: from the  delicious and consistent food quality to a relaxing and yet chic ambiance!!! Highly recommended !!!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: The tomato salad was the best part of the meal. The service was great, and the drinks were amazing.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Tried the lobster risotto and it was delicious!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: This was a birthday lunch for my business partner. It took quite a while for a waiter to greet us, and did us to get water and a bread basket. When our meals arrived, one of the orders was the wrong entree. Unfortunately. This resulted in my business partner having to wait 15 minutes to receive the correct order.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: C’était phénoménal, j’avais le loup de mer et les profiteroles après, les deux sont parfait.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: We had a wonderful bday lunch with 3 of us. We sat inside due to the heat. There were clear directional markers on the floor and all staff were wearing masks properly. Menu and payment were done contactless. We had a delicious meal starting with apps including escargot, onion soup, and beef tartare followed by yummy steak frites and veal plus celebratory desserts. I felt really safe dining here too - tons of space between tables.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Food was very good, this was the best Le Dip burger I have had. French onion soup, Mac gratin, steak tartare, foie gras cream were all on point. I thought the charcuterie plate was weird and could have used some cheese.Service was a huge disappointment, waiter didn't give us a menu walk. Had to flag down for missing items and to ask to order drinks. Felt like he was doing us a favor waiting on us.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Great Experience.  Excellent food and drinks!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Very classy - the absolute BEST bread 🥖 basket 🧺 in town!  Sooo happy that Sunday night special is soft shell crab 🦀

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Greeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeat

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Excellent food and service, as always!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Food was great. We were sitting outside on 14th so very very hot, so if you would like to sit outside, make sure it’s not on 14th!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Great! Food,service, ambiance

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Been here many times was so excited reopened for dining and will never return absolute worst service and mediocre at best food sad to see them reopen and be shell of what they were

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: They don’t have even disposable face masks for people who forgot their own - made us go buy one. For their price points that’s a bit greedy.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: We were celebrating a friend’s last few days living in DC. Not only was the food delicious, our server went out of her way to accommodate he group. She surprised us at the end of the meal with a plate of profiteroles with “Bon Voyage” written in chocolate. What a great evening and nice surprise. 5 stars!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: I'm glad that I called to make sure I had a table outside - there wasn't anything noted during the reservation process - because I didn't. I had to move up my reservation by 30 minutes for an outdoor table, which was fine. The table I asked for sat with the previous diners' glasses for 15 minutes before staff cleared and disinfected it. We were not seated until 10 minutes after our reservation time. Food was delicious as always, but service was a disappointment.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Sat way in the back, not used to that, but I guess someone has too. Waitress very sweet but a bit too chatty! We wanted to talk amongst ourselves.Food is always great!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: This is hands down our favorite restaurant in the DMV. As always, the beef bourguignon was outstanding and my husband loved his steak frites. Service was excellent, with us in and out in an hour (a plus when dining outdoors in the DC summer heat and humidity). I'm sure we could easily have lingered longer, but we passed on dessert because of the heat.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Good social distancing and Covid prevention steps that I saw being taken. Had the gazpacho and warm shrimp salad, absolutely delicious. Glad Le Dip is open again, will return.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Really appreciate all the safety precautions the restaurant has taken without compromising the consistently excellent service and food/drinks we’re accustomed to from Le Diplomate. Our server made sure our daughter’s birthday was a special one. Many thanks!!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: For several years we have made this an anniversary event.  The petit tower has been the main attraction. This year that was not the case and it was disappointing.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: The atmosphere and food was fantastic - they were great about my food allergies and the service was very attentive.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: The food delivered as it always does and they took extensive steps to ensure a safe environment while maintaining the ambiance.  Some menu items ran out early but that's to be expected given the current operating constraints.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Very safe !! Tables with social distance

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Terrific food and environment.  Will visit again soon.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: The staff are easily the best in the city. The spacing of the tables felt very safe. Food was delicious as always!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: We ate outside, great weather, good social distancing.  Food was really great. We had the lump crab appetizer and the Monday special, Dorade Royals en Papillote.  I’d forgot how great this restaurant is.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Excelente!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Our dining experience was very good. The waiter was very helpful in helping us to decide what to eat when we could not decide between several options. He also offered the best way to get our steak cooked.  The restaurant did have their tables set up for social distancing and every staff member was wearing a mask.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Be here many times but this time was terrible. Service was very poor and food was very average.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Not impressed. Crabcake was dry and and substandard, Mahi Mahi was small little piece with what tasted like thousand island dressing poured over it.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: The best dining experience around Never disappoints!

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Annie is my favorite server in Baltimore! Linwood’s is consistency excellent! The best chicken I’ve ever had anywhere!

Name: Linwoods
Comments: It was my wife’s birthday and we went to Linwood’s  to celebrate.  From our arrival at the beginning through the end of the meal, we had an excellent dining experience.

Name: Linwoods
Comments: Linwood’s is consistently an outstanding restaurant in all aspects particularly the creativity and quality of the food as well as the superior service. Their staff is so well trained!  I had two soft shell crabs (whale size) sautéed in a lemon butter sauce served over kernels of sweet corn and tiny tomatoes. I may not be describing the meal correctly but it was a WOW. I had decaf cappuccino and I like a dark rich roast. This was not but it did not mar the experience. Great restaurant!

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Outdoor dining is terrific!!!!!!  Raoul & Henri continue to do everything “just right”. Even in these crazy Covid days. J Dory fish dinner is so, so good and the best margaritas in town. Consistently the best meal in town.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: We went during the COVID lockdown. They set up tables out front on the sidewalk. It was our anniversary and they treated us special. Great food and service.

Name: Mistral - Sherman Oaks
Comments: Very COVID Friendly !  Outdoor tables... Well Spaced... VERY CLEAN... Food was A.M.A.Z.I.N.G. !! ... Had Gazpacho, Escargot, & Duck Confit.Can't say enough good things about Mistral.

Name: Parc
Comments: Always Great & Never Disappoints!!!

Name: Parc
Comments: Since we have to dine outdoors, it would be more comfortable if they-along with other restaurants-to have any type of air conditioning setup.

Name: Parc
Comments: Good restaurant. Overpriced food. Burger was good though.

Name: Parc
Comments: Dinner menu was limited. No Duck Confit or Lamb, which is why my party went to Parc in the first place. Server seemed disappointed that my party was seated at his table, until he realized the bill was going to be large. Once I asked for the bill, it took 15mins and me asking twice for the server to bring it over. The food was great. Back of the house and the hosts get 5 stars. The server gets 3. Overall, 4 stars.

Name: Parc
Comments: Great food!! Great service! Great outdoor dining!!!!

Name: Parc
Comments: Edwin was a great server; prompt & professional service. The food was great! I had the tuna carpaccio which I found to be light and so so good . My fiancé enjoyed the chicken club. He said the chicken was very flavorful. Parc is a beautiful setting & we had a great lunch to get our visit in Philadelphia started .

Name: Parc
Comments: I ordered the gazpacho soup. It was average and very overpriced for a very small portion. My friend ordered the chicken club, it had been sitting because the bread was discovered to be soggy on the bottom, so only one half was eaten, and the rest was not taken home. I love parc - I’ve been going there for years, I know Covid has had a deleterious effect on restaurants in Philadelphia, however, The cost Of the food for what is delivered is not what I can continue to endure.

Name: Parc
Comments: Had the tomato Basil salad with mozzarella and the Basil cocktail. Both amazing and refreshing. Perfect for a hot summer day. The serving staff were attentive and kind. Would definitely recommend.

Name: Parc
Comments: This is a great restaurant, but you can't fully appreciate it when you have to eat on the sidewalk.  The food is excellent.  The service is good, but they have to hustle you out of there quickly  (90 minutes).  If you're doing a major business transaction,  it's difficult because you have to rush it a bit.

Name: Parc
Comments: Fantastic as always! Thanks for the macaroons as a treat to our graduation. You guys are the best!

Name: Parc
Comments: We were there this past Sunday for brunch. Our waitress and the other support staff were so great despite the fact that it was about 100 degrees outside and all the tables were occupied. The restaurant seems to be doing a very good job of implementing social distancing while still providing a great experience.

Name: Parc
Comments: The staff was in a hurry to turn the table, and it was rude to do so while enjoying our food, a bottle of wine and an otherwise pleasant evening.

Name: Parc
Comments: The food and service was great.

Name: Parc
Comments: We loved it. Food was amazingly delicious. Service was excellent.

Name: Parc
Comments: Everything was wonderful from our drinks to our service.

Name: Parc
Comments: Zach was the best server we've had in a long time.  Courteous, fun, friendly.  Wonderful!

Name: Parc
Comments: Our server, Zach, provided us with literally the best service I have ever received dining out before! He made us feel very welcome, knew the menu and preparation of the food to a T, made recommendations for us and how we were going to go about our meal, and was just overall so fun and kind. Seriously, he was the best!!!

Name: Parc
Comments: Great experience Little disappointed they currently do not have cheese boards

Name: Parc
Comments: We ordered the escargot, which was excellent, for an appetizer. For dinner, we got the shrimp salad. The salad was fresh and the amount of shrimp was good but I didn't love the dressing. My boyfriend got the steak frites and thought it was amazing. The only downside was sitting outside because we were in direct sunlight, which got very hot. Otherwise, the service and food was very good.

Name: Parc
Comments: Great service even better food and wine

Name: Parc
Comments: great spot...looking forward to them opening the doors... street is getting old now.

Name: Parc
Comments: We enjoyed our experience at Parc! The food was great but it was our wedding anniversary. I let them know at the momento of the reservation but they didn't give us any special treat...

Name: Parc
Comments: The service and food at Park is wonderful.  They have always had out door dining available, but they have expanded on that space to give more distance between diners during this crazy time.

Name: Parc
Comments: Fantastic place. Parc remains excellent. That said, the service during the COVID pandemic is NOT what it usually is.

Name: Parc
Comments: Great food as always but bring back veuve clicquot by the glass!

Name: Parc
Comments: Garage validation should be considered if spending greater than 100.00Staff needs to be more astute about moving the homeless along that r bothering people eating outside

Name: Parc
Comments: We thoroughly enjoyed our meal at Parc.  For a brief second we forgot about the pandemic.  Everything around us seems to be changing.  Except nothing has changed about the food and service at Parc - - still excellent.

Name: Parc
Comments: Very pleased with the service ESPECIALLY considering the covid restrictions - the restaurant is always A+ and a favorite of ours.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: So classic Hollywood.  (Even though its Beverly Hills.)

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Food was terrible. We all ordered the same salad (4) the McCarthy Salad, and it was served mushed, could barely recognize anything in it, seemed like it was almost blended .  Terrible.The drinks were good though!Needless to say, definitely put a damper on our lunch/afternoon

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Even COVID 19 cannot detract from the beautiful outdoor setting used for their famous Sunday Brunch.  We felt, for a brief few hours, that the world was normal again.  Thank you for the magnificent food, excellent service and perfect ambience for our special occasion.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: The Polo Lounge is always a lovely place to dine. Sunday was very pricey, however, & it’s already $$$$.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Perfect. Very hospitable and all staff were wearing proper protection.

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Fantastic a perfect summer setting, social distancing and hygiene protocols observed. Thank you for a perfect experience!

Name: Polo Lounge @ The Beverly Hills Hotel
Comments: Always perfect 🇺🇸

Name: PRESS
Comments: Amazing atmosphere, food, and service. It was worth it.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Press is an absolute MUST for anybody visiting the Napa Valley. Every dining experience there is a memorable delight!

Name: PRESS
Comments: The staff were very attentive.  The brunch/lunch menu was super limited and the description for the items listed by staff was not consistent with what came out of their kitchen.  Overall this place was ok but did not live up to the reviews we read or the type of dining experience we paid for.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Yummy food with great service! Came here for the first time with my husband  for lunch and wasn’t disappointed. The outdoor seating is beautiful , and our server made great recommendations.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Not enough food for the cost. We came for our 1 year anniversary (a splurge meal) we left hungry and broke. Food was just “ok” but small portions. I had half a chicken with maybe a handle full of salad and was $37?!  Bread cost extra and fries was $19 a la cart?! My husband had what I would call a pulled pork sandwich (served alone) at $22. Then was lovely patio seating but they need to do something about ALL the flies. It was obnoxious trying to shu them alway the whole meal. We left here and shared a burger at Gotts just to fill up.  Note we spent $175 for lunch. Wanted  to support local business. But unfortunately, won’t be coming back.

Name: PRESS
Comments: Press is a great place to go for date night, special occasion, getting together with friends, or for everyday dining. It never disappoints. The food is delicious and presented so beautifully, and the service is always great. They have the largest list of Napa wines in the valley that includes many older vintages

Name: PRESS
Comments: Excellent.  Favorite restaurant in Napa.  Great wine list

Name: PRESS
Comments: Outstanding service - the food was delicious. Loved the outdoor seating. Thank you!

Name: PRESS
Comments: Absurdly overpriced for tiny portions of overly complicated food! FOAM is not a food! No longer serving the chopped salad and delicious side dishes they used to have. Save your money- definitely NOT worth it!

Name: PRESS
Comments: Food was good as always - this is one of our favorite places

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Had a great time at Riccardo Enoteca! Due to the current restrictions on dining in Chicago, the only available seating for the restaurant is outside on the sidewalk lining the restaurant. The street is very cute and was not busy. Out server was very friendly and knowledgeable about the food. We enjoyed the Caprese salad and the grilled octopus. I had for my entre the sea bass and it was pretty good as well! Great place for a date.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Great service and wonderful food. I loved the trout, with a nice red sauce and veggies. Lovely ambiance on the patio.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Food was very good but not sure it’s worth going back again given how many Italian places there are in the city. Service was not great... very pushy and made a super rude comment about us ordering so much food.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Food was tasty, service was good, and the expanded outdoor space was attractive for this pandemic summer.  A minor negative is that noise levels from the street, from police sirens and motorcycles, was a bit distracting.  Highly recommended.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Wonderful first time experience. Friendly staff...

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Just the best! Always a favorite.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Birthday.   It’s a tradition for us.  We always celebrate my husbands birthday at RL and we have never been disappointed!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: A truly gracious place that makes you feel special for just showing up. Everything about it is wonderful. Beautiful place, perfect food and welcoming servers.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: If looking for a place to enjoy a romantic evening, RL the Restaurant is the place. The service and the food was excellent. Very accommodating making sure whatever I needed was quickly provided. Safe environment considering COVID19 .

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Everything was great. We were outside and tucked away distanced from the other tables. Happy to be back!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: I had a wonderful birthday dinner at RL. The manager Michael went above and beyond to make sure we felt welcomed and attended to. The restaurant decor is truly remarkable and the servers have a plethora of knowledge regarding the vast quantity of wine and spirits they have available. My Rosé was light and airy and the steak melted in my mouth.  Overall I had such a great experience and I would go again on another special occasion.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: RL is a special and unique dinning experience! I highly recommend!

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Lunch with the girlfriend. We sat outside, only thing noted, mosquitos were really bad. Maybe put out some plants to help with that.

Name: RL Restaurant
Comments: Our server had a special kid item made for us. Menu is smaller. Service is always excellent.

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: Marvelous as always.  Paco makes everyone feel like family!

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: Dinner was delicious, highly recommend this place.

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: Make eating here every time we visit Galveston. Best seafood, amazing service & always enjoy quiet dining experience

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: Phenomenal food and excellent service! Really great place to eat if you’re in the Galveston area!

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: Excellent menu selection combined with first rate service

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: Best eats winner for me on Galveston Island!  Fine dining, excellence with ambience,  unparalleled service - altogether superb dining unmatched by others!

Name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Baton Rouge
Comments: Amazing service and food! Fun place to celebrate special occasions

Name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Baton Rouge
Comments: Great food and distancing was perfect. Great attention to all details

Name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Baton Rouge
Comments: Because of Covid-19, we had to wait until now, to celebrate three occasions that happened on May 10th. It was our 51 anniversary, Mother’s Day, and my 4th anniversary for getting a kidney transplant.  All were on the same day.   The experience, as usual, was perfect. Nothing to suggest for improvement.  Thanks for such a great experience.

Name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Baton Rouge
Comments: Great service and food. Best experience in Baton Rouge.

Name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Baton Rouge
Comments: Fantastic as always!

Name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Baton Rouge
Comments: Staff were wonderful and the food was impeccable as always. Finally got to enjoy a night out!

Name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Baton Rouge
Comments: Our waitress Dana was just amazing!We love your place!!

Name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Baton Rouge
Comments: Great lunch! Madelaine was professional and very accommodating!

Name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Baton Rouge
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: Phenomenal meal

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: excellent French dinner; I had coquille st jacques and duck; my wife had the duck salad

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: My wife and I were celebrating our wedding anniversary and had a delicious meal and overall great experience.  Would highly recommend to a friend.

Name: Saint Jacques French Cuisine
Comments: At first glance you wouldn’t think you were entering a place with a romantic atmosphere and delectable food due to the location in a shopping mall, but don’t be fooled! This place is amazing! The food is unbelievable and the service is incredible. Wonderful anniversary dinner for us :)

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: It was great

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: The service was very slow and the quality of the sushi rolls has really declined.  Just not a meal worth the price tag.

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: The whole fish is a must!!!

Name: Shinsei Restaurant
Comments: Always amazed by the quality of the staff and ambiance.

Name: Sotto
Comments: The epitome of a first class establishment and it’s inexpensive. A must stop every time I’m near Cincinnati

Name: Sotto
Comments: Wonderful meal. Excellent service. Highly recommend.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Sotto
Comments: Fantastic server with lots of friendly energy and absolutely delicious food. The goat cheese honey bread was as crave-able as expected, and the short rib dish was definitely a show stopper for us. Topped it off with the ricotta donuts and a couple of their very drinkable barrel-aged bourbon cocktails.  We will be returning!!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Delicious, as always- we enjoy Sotto as a date night or a dinner for special occasions and the food did not disappoint!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Service was impeccable. Every dish tasted fantastic. Our server talked me into the newest bread, nduja con broccolo, it was delectable.

Name: Sotto
Comments: We had our engagement dinner here. The food was excellent and the staff was so accommodating. They made our night very special. Such a unique atmosphere as well, loved the "basement" setting!

Name: Sotto
Comments: First time trying Sotto, definitely will not be the last.  Food was fantastic, our server Hillary was even better.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Music did not fit ambiance . Food was delicious, but overpriced for portions.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Good food. Little pricey. Nice staff, but took forever to get our check. Would recommend though.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Nice visit but I would dine another place in the area for the price

Name: Sotto
Comments: Really enjoyed this restaurant. Cappalacci was outstandingGoat cheese appetizer was deliciousDon’t forget to get the ricotta donuts!Definitely would go backGet reservations well in advance

Name: Sotto
Comments: Everything was amazing.  Top notch from start to finish, being in the industry we appreciated being able to get out relax and have a great night.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Awesome food & service! Music not appropriate for this type restaurant. Too much metal rock, and too loud.

Name: Sotto
Comments: As usual, Sotto was perfection from start to finish!

Name: Sotto
Comments: What an amazing place to celebrate or just go out for a delicious dinner! Get the short rib cappellacci!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Amazing food and great service. Servers were very kind and considerate also with the social distancing situation.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: As always, our experience was great, if unusual due to Covid pandemic. All staff was careful & made certain we as guests we, as well. Our table was distant from the next patrons. We felt safe & well cared for!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: I have been coming to Spinasse since 2013 and they are one of the most consistent restaurants that I’ve ever had the pleasure of coming to. I get one dish practically every single time. That’s right. The tajarin con burro e salvia I’ve been having for 7 years. The consistency of that dish is incredible. I’ve tasted other dishes when I’ve come with friends, and they were wonderful, but to be able to do simplicity in a high-end way speaks volumes in my book. With the world travels I’ve had, eating at Michelin star restaurants, and paying upwards of $200+ for myself for dinner, I still come back to Spinasse to have a big or small bowl of pasta that I haven’t been able to taste anywhere else, some wonderful wine, and experience the wonderful service. You won’t go wrong in coming to, and experiencing the flavors of Spinasse.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: The food and wine pairing at St Francis is a must when traveling to Sonoma. The care in which the chef paired the food with wine was superb.  The staff walked us through every course at the right cadence and we were allowed to savor each bite and each pairing.  The menu changes slightly every two weeks so I hate to elaborate on a particular dish but know that this experience is worth every minute and dollar spent!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: betty and I have been members for 25 years.  it's one of the most beautiful settings in wine country. new chef and food and wine pairing staff were great.  under the circumstances of covid 19, it was spectacular dining experience.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: If you are looking to celebrate a special occasion I highly recommend the Stone House! The location is beautiful, and I love the rustic elegance of the Stone House.

Name: Stonehouse at San Ysidro Ranch
Comments: We love eating under the Loquat trees! I also can’t live without the tortilla soup every so often. The menu is quite limited right now, so entree choices are few. The bread with the seasoned olive oil is excellent. This is simply a wonderful place for the atmospheric alone!

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: I was thrilled with everything about Season to Go (Taste.) Living very close to there, I intend to make it a regular stop. All of the staff were delightful and the service was impeccable.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: The staff handled the rain storm very professional and made it as pleasant as possible to wrap our meals to go!

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Wedding anniversary

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: This was my 3rd time in less than 2 weeks and I loved it! The food is incredible

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Was excellent . Great service, great food

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Can't go wrong with Talula's!!!   You must go :-)

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Out of the many COVID times outdoor restaurants i've been to, Talula's diner ambiance is the best... but the servers not exactly the best. A little hostile, with an attitude, and from the moment we sat down he was rushing us to order and get out quickly. Loved it, but will NEVER go back. There's always Positano with live music and much better food and servers and overall experience :)

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: The evening in the garden was perfect. The scallops and the short ribs all succulent. The service was attentive and not obtrusive. Hot summer night with a beautiful breeze. Love the music! Thanks for making our evening perfect.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Great ambiance in the garden. Good service and nice menu

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Excellent food, cocktails, and service! I went for brunch I will go back try dinner next time!

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Covid friendly! Very spaced out. Felt safe, comfortable and relaxed. The breeze in the garden! Brunch was spectacular! Omelette with melted Brie, grilled peach pancakes, fresh raspberry muffin homemade butter, grits w/ maple butter...crisp wine. Service was exceptional. First restaurant we went to since Covid and felt normal! Loved every minute!

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: In the midst of COVID I felt completely at ease with the precautions being taken by the entire staff.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: One of the best spots in the city

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Sat outside.  Lovely evening,  Superb service.  Excellent food - highly recommend the ginger carrot soup, scallops and succotash, and ravioli.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Great job on navigating outdoor dining and safety. Excellent service. Food as good as always. It was so nice being out in Philly on a summer Saturday night. Highly recommend.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: There to celebrate the soon to be marriage of friends and Talulas was outstanding in every way. First, they take your temperature using an iPad like device, which is both cool and futuristic too. We said outdoors in their main outdoor space, and the ambience is fantastic. Will go back time and again!

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Great food and service but seating can be rough during COVID. The garden area is beautiful (and half the reason to come) but we ended up sitting at a table on the sidewalk far away from the garden. It really look away from the overall experience.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: These days, we eat outside at restaurants.  We were temperature scanned as we entered.  The spacing of tables in Talula's Garden seemed appropriate for safe distancing.  The staff all wore masks and minimized the direct contact with dishes etc., during our meal.  I felt perfectly safe.The food was fabulous.  Our group of 4 had scallops, short ribs, and salmon for entrées, wonderful beet salad for appetizer. Nice sweets for finish.The weather was very hot, but the garden courtyard in the shade made the dinner fairly comfortable.  We're going back!

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Delicious, fresh food and excellent service. First time at Talula’s Garden and I’d definitely return.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: We had an outstanding experience.  We felt very safe and comfortable eating outdoors with good social distancing between tables.  The service was excellent and our food arrived quickly - including a side we ordered as an appetizer, which arrived just a minute or two after we ordered it (our daughter LOVES cornbread).  I had the short rib.  It was beautifully cooked and tender, and the portion size was quite large.  The flavorful, hearty sauce really tied the dish together.  We all left full and happy.  10/10, we will be going back.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: I love Talula's! I could eat the scallop dish for dinner every night. Thank you to the whole staff for working during these crazy times, and making it just perfect.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Excellent food and ambiance. Very safe social distancing protocols.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Food was incredible and once again we had a fantastic server. Loved being in the outside garden.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Lovely patio setting. Delicious cheese plate and the scallops and succotash were very tasty

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: great job with outdoor dining and delivering excellent food

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Wonderful! Loved their outside seating. Felt very comfortable

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Wonderful experience.  The food was excellent, service friendly, beautiful ambience.  Highly recommended for a special evening.

Name: Talula’s Garden
Comments: Lovely evening in a special spot with beautifully composed food.

Name: The Metro Wine Bar & Bistro
Comments: Consistency is the key.  Always well prepared food and service is tops.

Name: The Metro Wine Bar & Bistro
Comments: As always, one of the best restaurants in OKC delivers. The avocado cucumber soup is an instant classic, a must-try in this town.  Mushroom ravioli and veal potstickers great for starts or small entree.  The risotto with braised beef is cooked perfectly and the seasonal salmon will make you question every salmon dish you’ve had before. Highest recommendations.

Name: The Metro Wine Bar & Bistro
Comments: Our server & meal were excellent, we always enjoy dining at The Metro!

Name: The Metro Wine Bar & Bistro
Comments: Outstanding as always!!

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: It was a good experience and was able to sit outside

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Felt very safe here eating during the pandemic. Food was great! I have gluten, dairy, and shellfish dietary restrictions. I felt like I had great options to choose from. I love that the menu is based on an anti-inflammatory diet. Can’t wait to go back!

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: delicious healthy food in a wonderfully casual but classy setting

Name: True Food Kitchen - Chicago
Comments: Delicious food and friendly, impeccable service as always.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Uchi lived up to the hype! It was an amazing meal, and our server, Bryan, was absolutely fabulous.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: We were quickly seated upon arrival for our reservation. Our waiter, James was polite and welcoming which I wouldn’t expect anything less. My date and I ordered the 10-course tasting – ultimate chef’s choice and it was nice that James asked questions about our likes and dislikes and what we enjoy more of. James also asked if it was okay to have other people bring out the dish and/or pick up the plates. I was absolutely fine with the question but found it made the dining experience with different servers less personal by the end of the night. The other staff that brought the plates were polite but I wish they took the time to elaborate on the meal(s) instead of making a rushed dull statement; it would have made the omakase experience more polished. James checked on us often but I’m still puzzled why there are numerous people to drop off and pick up the plates. It’s a small concern since the tip was between 18%-20% on Omakase pricing and I’m not sure if it’s split among those who approached our table or strictly our server; it seems like a team effort. Overall, James is really great. The dining experience is nice; I enjoyed having the lights dimmed for a while then lighting up the room which shifted the ambiance. The lighting seemed to rotate every time a new plate arrived to our table which set the mood for the new tasting. (Not sure if that's on purpose or if it was coincidence.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Delicious meals and cocktails! Best happy hour in Dallas!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Food was amazing but had to wait a little between courses but overall worth going back.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: We had an excellent experience! They really make an effort to customize your experience! The service was outstanding and the food phenomenal!

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: They put the priority service to customer who came behind me.Try to push us to the dark corner of the yard even we reversed 1 week before.The outside area is very Dark and leak of light. we did not see our meal at 9.00 pmSushi and sashimi is very fresh good taste.I think 1.5 star is enough for service attitude.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Travis was our waiter and he was amazing. He very kindly explained the process to us as we were first timers. He was attentive to financial issues and recommended great wines. The timing of the food arrival was some of the best I’ve ever experienced in America. They allowed us to linger and enjoy the company without feeling rushed and never left us with an empty plate or glass along the way. It was a magnificent experience to have them pick new things for us based on the things we explained we liked. We would go back in a second.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: The food was good however we were disappointed in the service. We felt dismissed and as though we were an inconvenience.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Food is amazing as always. SERVICE SUCKS AND IS GETTING WORSE. I asked for soy sauce and wasabi from 3 people and not one person got me some. For a restaurant this expensive you would expect better service or at least someone get you soy said and wasabi to have with your shashimi.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Food is amazing! Everything we tried was delectable including day boat scallops and rolls and happy hour beef dish. Kara kuyri is a delicious drink but not sure if it has much alcohol though... Will definitely keep coming back. :)

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Santiago was amazing.  Made it a great night.

Name: Uchi - Dallas
Comments: Uchi always delivers great service and food!

Name: UMI
Comments: OMG.... this restaurant is absolutely AWESOME!!!! They have come up with a fun whimsical way to enforce social distancing.... with beautiful statues donned with interesting headgear having dinner next to ya.To give ya an idea of how succulent the food was... my 2 year old son & I came here for dinner two nights out of the four we were here for vacation. My favorite sushi items were the specialty sushi like sake aioli and yellowtail/otoro caviar. If you can’t decide which to get, I recommend the otoro b/c it just melts in your mouth! The aburi sushi were good, but I have had better at other Japanese restaurants.The wagyu beef was absolutely divine!! It’s pretty pricey at $33/oz (minimum 2 oz) but TOTALLY worth it! I think it was better than the Kobe beef I had in Kobe, Japan! The Chilean sea bass was a little dry but great flavor. The fluffy cheesecake was good but didn’t like the banana glaze that it was soaked in.This is my new favorite Japanese rest!!
